# Quality Gaps – Lessons from Real Driver Testing

## Observed Patterns
- Incomplete test coverage due to ownership changes
- Test execution without peer review
- Late defect discovery during integration

## Root Causes
- Test status prioritized over coverage
- Missing review checkpoints
- Unclear ownership boundaries

## Preventive Practices
- Mandatory test case reviews
- Coverage-based completion criteria
- Clear ownership and handover rules
- Release gates tied to risk, not deadlines

## Senior Insight
Most quality issues originate from
process gaps rather than individual mistakes.

